"title": "2525: Jesus Christ, cross of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2525: jesus christ, cross of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The death of Jesus Christ is of central importance to the Christian faith. Through Christ's death, sinners are reconciled to God and to their fellow human beings. Paul summarises the gospel as “the message of the cross”.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ foretold his death on the cross</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:18-Matt20:19\">MAT 20:18–20:19</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:33-Mark10:34\">MRK 10:33–10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31-Luke18:32\">LUK 18:31–18:32</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:2\">MAT 26:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:14-John3:15\">JHN 3:14–3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:28\">JHN 8:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:32-John12:33\">JHN 12:32–12:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:32\">JHN 18:32</a></p>\n<h2>The facts of Jesus Christ's death on the cross</h2>\n<h3>Carrying Jesus Christ's cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:17\">JHN 19:17</a></strong> <em>Though Jesus Christ began to carry his cross, the Romans soon forced Simon of Cyrene to continue with it.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:32\">MAT 27:32</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:21\">MRK 15:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:26\">LUK 23:26</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ refused the comfort of wine, which would have lessened the pains of his suffering</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:34\">MAT 27:34</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:23\">MRK 15:23</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ was nailed to the cross</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:33\">LUK 23:33</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:35\">MAT 27:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:24-Mark15:25\">MRK 15:24–15:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:18\">JHN 19:18</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's words from the cross</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:34\">LUK 23:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:43\">LUK 23:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:26-John19:27\">JHN 19:26–19:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:46\">MAT 27:46</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:34\">MRK 15:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1\">PSA 22:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:46\">LUK 23:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:28-John19:30\">JHN 19:28–19:30</a></p>\n<h3>Signs accompanying Jesus Christ's death on the cross</h3>\n<p>Darkness over the whole land for three hours:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:45\">MAT 27:45</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:33\">MRK 15:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:44-Luke23:45\">LUK 23:44–23:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:51\">MAT 27:51</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:38\">MRK 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:45\">LUK 23:45</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:52-Matt27:53\">MAT 27:52–27:53</a> <em>the dead come back to life</em></p>\n<h2>People at the scene of the cross</h2>\n<p>The Roman centurion and his men:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:35-Matt27:36\">MAT 27:35–27:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:54\">MAT 27:54</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:39\">MRK 15:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:47\">LUK 23:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:38\">MAT 27:38</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:27\">MRK 15:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:32-Luke23:33\">LUK 23:32–23:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:18\">JHN 19:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:44\">MAT 27:44</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:39-Luke23:43\">LUK 23:39–23:43</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:39-Matt27:43\">MAT 27:39–27:43</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:29-Mark15:32\">MRK 15:29–15:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:35-Luke23:37\">LUK 23:35–23:37</a> <em>people who insulted and mocked Jesus Christ</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:55-Matt27:56\">MAT 27:55–27:56</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:40-Mark15:41\">MRK 15:40–15:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:27-Luke23:31\">LUK 23:27–23:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:25\">JHN 19:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:49\">LUK 23:49</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:26-John19:27\">JHN 19:26–19:27</a> <em>John</em></p>\n<h2>Responsibility for the cross</h2>\n<h3>The cross as God's plan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23\">ACT 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:10\">ISA 53:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:42\">MAT 26:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:30-John14:31\">JHN 14:30–14:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:25-Acts4:28\">ACT 4:25–4:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:1-Ps2:2\">PSA 2:1–2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:8\">REV 13:8</a></p>\n<h3>The crowd's call for Jesus Christ's crucifixion</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:21-Matt27:22\">MAT 27:21–27:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:12-Mark15:14\">MRK 15:12–15:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:18-Luke23:21\">LUK 23:18–23:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:15\">JHN 19:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:25\">MAT 27:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:36\">ACT 2:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:14-1Thess2:15\">1TH 2:14–2:15</a></p>\n<h3>Jewish and Roman leaders' responsibility</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:1\">MAT 27:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:20\">MAT 27:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:11\">MRK 15:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:26\">MAT 27:26</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:15\">MRK 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:16\">JHN 19:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:24-Luke23:25\">LUK 23:24–23:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:6-John19:7\">JHN 19:6–19:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:10\">ACT 4:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:8\">1CO 2:8</a></p>\n<h2>The triumph of the cross</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:15\">COL 2:15</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The cross brings glory to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:1\">JHN 17:1</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ refers to his approaching death, the climax of his earthly life.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:28\">JHN 12:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:31-John13:32\">JHN 13:31–13:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:5\">JHN 17:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:8-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:8–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:2\">HEB 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:8-Rev5:14\">REV 5:8–5:14</a></p>\n<h3>The cross brings reconciliation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:13-Eph2:17\">EPH 2:13–2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:9-Rom5:10\">ROM 5:9–5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18-2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:18–5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:20\">COL 1:20</a></p>\n<h3>Identification with the crucified Christ releases believers from their old way of life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:5-Rom6:13\">ROM 6:5–6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:24-Gal5:25\">GAL 5:24–5:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:14\">GAL 6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13-Col2:14\">COL 2:13–2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's cross is central to the Christian message</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:2\">1CO 2:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:23-Acts2:24\">ACT 2:23–2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13\">ACT 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:30\">ACT 5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:27-Acts13:29\">ACT 13:27–13:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:1\">GAL 3:1</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's cross is the symbol of Christian discipleship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24\">MAT 16:24</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34\">MRK 8:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23\">LUK 9:23</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:38\">MAT 10:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:18-John21:19\">JHN 21:18–21:19</a></p>",
